# Strict Jetpack Compose Best Practices (MeApp Android)

## 1. File and Composable Structure
- **One Composable per File:** Do not declare more than one `@Composable` per file. *(Exception: You may include multiple `@Preview` composables in the same file to preview the main composable.)*
- **Preview Requirement:** Every Compose file must contain at least one preview composable using the `@PreviewTheme` annotation, which previews the main composable.

## 2. Imports and Usage
- **No Fully Qualified Names:** Never use a full package name for any child composable (e.g., write `Text()`, not `androidx.compose.material3.Text()`). Always import the required package instead.

## 3. Design System Enforcement
- **Design System Only:** Use only design system resources (fonts, colors, spacing, radius, shadows, typography, etc.) from the `@theme` folder. *Never hardcode static values.*
- **Shared Composables First:** Always use shared composables from the `@connect` folder before using Material composables. Only use Material3 components if no shared version exists.

## 4. Static String Management
- **No Hardcoded Static Text:** All static text content (labels, titles, subtitles, button text, error messages, etc.) used in a composable must be declared in a dedicated PascalCase `Strings` object in a separate file under a `strings` subfolder in the same package as the composable (e.g., `features/{feature}/strings/AppHelpModalStrings.kt`).
- **Strings Folder:** If the `strings` folder does not exist, create it under the direct folder of the feature/component (e.g., `features/{feature}/strings`).
- **PascalCase Naming:** The string object and all constants must use PascalCase (e.g., `AppHelpModalStrings.Title`).
- **Usage:** Always reference static text from the corresponding `Strings` object. Never hardcode static text in composables.
- **Scope:** This applies to all composables in the `features` and `components` folders. For shared/common strings, use a `CommonStrings.kt` in the relevant shared package.
- **Exception:** Static text used in `@PreviewTheme` composables may remain inline for preview/demo purposes only.

## 5. Design Fidelity
- **Figma/Images:** If a Figma link is provided, use the Figma MCP and ensure pixel-perfect design, using the design system from `@theme`.
- **Image Reference:** If an image reference is provided, match the pixel design and use the design system from `@theme`.

## 6. Clarification
- **Unclear Requirements:** If anything is unclear, ask clarifying questions before generating code.

## 7. Exceptions
- **Preview Composables:** Multiple `@Preview` composables are allowed in a file, but only for previewing the main composable.
- **Material3 Components:** Use Material3 components only if no shared version exists in `@connect`.
- **Imports:** If a composable is not available via import (e.g., generated or dynamic), explain the exception in a code comment.

---

**Summary:**
- One main composable per file, with previews.
- Always use `@PreviewTheme` for previews.
- Never use fully qualified names for composables.
- Use only design system resources from `@theme`.
- Prefer shared composables from `@connect` over Material3.
- Match Figma/image design exactly using the design system.
- Ask clarifying questions if requirements are unclear.
- Briefly explain any exceptions in code comments or documentation.
- **All static text must be in a PascalCase object in a dedicated strings file under a `strings` subfolder in the same package as the composable. No hardcoded static text.**
- **Exception: Static text in `@PreviewTheme` composables may remain inline for preview/demo purposes.**
